From David Davidian Subject Accounts of Anti Armenian Human Right Violations in Azerbaijan Accounts of Anti Armenian Human Right Violations in Azerbaijan Prelude to Current Events in Nagorno Karabakh I asked What's going on He says What's the matter can't you see they've overturned a car and they're killing Armenians DEPOSITION OF ZAVEN ARMENAKOVICH BADASIAN Born Employed Sumgait Bulk Yarn Plant Resident at Building Apartment Microdistrict Sumgait Azerbaijan On February my wife and I went to Baku to go shopping and returned to Sumgait at around five in the We ran into one of my relatives at the bus station and got to A lot of people had gathered not far away near the Well at first we didn't know what was happening and then a fellow I know comes up to me an Azerbaijani guy and says What are you standing here for Go home immediately I asked What's going on He says What's the matter can't you see they've overturned a car and they're killing Armenians He helped me catch a cab and we got home We sat at home for two During that time a gang of bandits came into our But the neighbors wouldn't let them in the There were about of They had sticks and pieces of armatures in their They were shouting something but you couldn't understand It wasn't one voice or two all of them were shouting in a They turned toward Building They went up to the third floor and we see that they're breaking glass and throwing things out the After a while they come out the entryway one has a pair of jeans in his hands another has a tape recorder and a third a They went on toward the auto parts We had to save After midnight on March we went to hide at School which is in Microdistrict There were two other Armenian families there with There were of us Out of all of them I had only known Ernest before he had moved to Sumgait from The Azerbaijani guard at the school let us At first he didn't want to but there was nowhere else for us to We had to plead with him and talk him into We were told that on that day the there would be an attack on our We went upstairs to a classroom on the second On the city radio station they announced three telephone numbers that could be used to summon assistance or communicate anything I called one of them and the First Secretary of the Sumgait City Party Committee I asked him for I say We're in School we need to be Well he says Got it wait there I'm sending out help I know his The First Secretary had been to our plant I had spoken with him When I called he said Muslimzade About two hours after the call we heard shouts near the We looked out the window and about to people were outside saying Armenians come out we're here to get They have clubs axes and armature shafts in their The guard sat there with us and asked Where should I go I say If your life is of any value to you you'll go down there and say that the Armenians were here and that they That's what he He went down there and said The Armenians were here he said I let them out the back door they went that And pointed with his And with shouts and noise the mob set off in the direction he had So the assistance we had been promised did They sent us help all right Instead of sending real soldiers he had sent his I am positive that Muslimzade did No one had seen us entering the school no one knew that we were In any case we stayed at the school until seven in the morning and no soldiers of any sort came to our In the morning we went to my relative's in Microdistrict and the soldiers took us to the SK club from The club was jammed with people and there were lots of people ahead of us there was no space One small boy about three months old died right in my There wasn't a single doctor The boy was uninjured there were no wounds or bruises on He was just very They gave him mouth to mouth resuscitation they did everything they could under the circumstances but were unable to save And his mother and father a young Armenian couple were right there on the floor I searched for a spot for us in the SK we have a small child of our own I wanted to find a room or something to put my family I went up to the third floor there were a lot of soldiers up there bandaged with canes limping with their heads broken They were a terrible Young guys all of There were a lot of bandaged Armenians Everyone had been beaten everyone was crying wailing and calling for I think that the City Party Committee ignored us True there was a snack bar a sausage was kopeks or kopeks a package of cookies that cost kopeks was being sold for a bottled soft drink cost a ruble But there was no way to get the things any I met my old uncle Aram Mikhailovich He saw me and tears welled up in his My whole life he had told me that we were friendly peoples that we worked together he always had Azerbaijanis over at his And now he saw me and there was nothing he could say he just You can understand his feelings of April Yerevan reference The Sumgait Tragedy Pogroms against Armenians in Soviet Azerbaijan Volume I Eyewitness Accounts edited by Samuel Shahmuradian forward by Yelena Bonner published by Aristide Caratzas NY pages David Davidian Armenia has not learned a lesson in Center for Regional Studies Anatolia and has forgotten the Box punishment inflicted on Cambridge MA Late Turkish President Turgut Ozal